ACTIONS CLASS
We use actions class in selenium to perform the mouse and keyboard actions. 

- doubleClick 
- right click 
- drag and drop 
- move to element


WebDriver driver=new ChromeDriver(); 

Actions actions=new Actions(driver); 

We need to use the perform() method after using any mouse and keyboard action on the page.

Actions class method 

contextClick() --> it performs the right click action on the current location of the mouse. 

contextClick(WebElement) --> performs the right click action in the middle of given webelement.

moveToElement(WebElement) --> it will move your mouse in the middle of given webelement

doubleClick(); --> it will perform double click action on the current location of the mouse
 
doubleClick(WebElement); --> it will perform double click action in the middle of given web element. 

// TASK: Navigate to the page and find all click and doubleclick buttons on the page

clickAndHold() --> it will click and hold the mouse left button 

release() --> it will release the clicked element 

dragAndDrop(source, target) --> this method drag and drop the element from source to target location. 


















